column5: Oh the boss is going to give ya an    kicking for that.

I cut my teeth on the original Lake Simcoe board after learning about it from Chris' (the originator's) dad at the little dock beside the bridge over the Holland River at hwy 11 at Bradford...  Sad to see the way a couple of yo-yos can get away with ruining a board without the admins stepping up and banishing them...

That would be the understatement of this season on that board. I'd like to see what a couple of those vegetables look like, probably genetically modified.
Not working from here either. Maybe Spiel is Special. Im on Rogers too.

I was on in the morning but can't get on now, I'm with Bell.  To add to the discussion, it is absolutely idiotic what's gone on for the last few months.  There has to be a simple way to delete problem people -- there's some great folks on there who would be more than happy to moderate, and would do a great job of it.  The site has helped me more than any other -- I live in Barrie, so fishing Lake Simcoe is very convenient, but simply can't be done successfully without some guidance.  Insane that a few extreme people can ruin a board so easily...

and that site gets far more hits then anyone seems to know  I post an underwater video on this site and it get 100 to 400 hits when I post it on that site I get 800 to 2000 hits....one heck of a lot of people just look on that site  it would be a money maker if done right
